    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>
                <date>4 Sepr. 1845</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Your letter to <persName>Mr Joseph<lb/> Jonas</persName> prest. of
                the Hebrew Institute of <date>24th</date> ult is at hand<lb/> and I have to thank
                you for the attention and trouble<lb/> you have been to for our Society I beg to
                inform<lb/> you that as our plan has not yet entirely matured we<lb/> are unable to
                enter into any final arrangements as regards<lb/> engaging a Teacher at present No
                one is perhaps more<lb/> aware than yourself of the difficulties attending the<lb/>
                establishing such an Institution and I much fear if we<lb/> do not meet with more
                harming and assistance than we<lb/> have already the laudable project will have to
                be abandoned</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I am Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Yours Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">Lewis Abraham</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Secretary</p>
        </body>
    </text>
